%% 4. Sequence Diagram: Scheduled Drift Check and Reconcile
sequenceDiagram
    participant Cron as Scheduler / CronJob
    participant Pipe as Drift Pipeline Script
    participant IaC as IaC Repo (Terraform)
    participant Cloud as Cloud / Infra
    participant API as FastAPI Backend
    participant DB as SQLite DB
    participant FE as React Frontend
    participant Op as Operator

    Cron->>Pipe: Trigger drift check (scheduled)
    Pipe->>IaC: Read desired state / plan
    Pipe->>Cloud: Fetch actual state
    Pipe->>Pipe: Compare desired vs actual
    Pipe->>API: POST /api/events (drift events)
    API->>DB: Insert DriftEvent & AuditEntry
    API-->>Pipe: 201 Created / summary

    Op->>FE: Open dashboard / refresh
    FE->>API: GET /api/metrics
    FE->>API: GET /api/events?status=pending
    API->>DB: Query events & metrics
    DB-->>API: Result set
    API-->>FE: JSON (events, metrics)
    FE-->>Op: Render drift list & KPIs

    Op->>FE: Click "Reconcile" on event
    FE->>API: POST /api/events/{id}/action (reconcile)
    API->>DB: Update DriftEvent, insert AuditEntry
    API-->>FE: Action result (e.g., pending/ok)


%% 5. Sequence Diagram: Demo Data Seeding
sequenceDiagram
    participant FE as Frontend (React)
    participant API as Backend (FastAPI)
    participant DB as SQLite DB

    FE->>API: POST /api/seed (optional params: count, reset)
    API->>DB: (Optional) DELETE existing events/audit (if reset)
    API->>DB: INSERT synthetic DriftEvent records
    API->>DB: INSERT corresponding AuditEntry records
    DB-->>API: Insert OK
    API-->>FE: { message, total }
    FE->>API: GET /api/metrics, /api/events
    API->>DB: Query metrics & events
    DB-->>API: Result set
    API-->>FE: JSON


